    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The database stores a block locator of the chain the database is synced to so that the index can efficiently determine the point it last stopped at. A locator is used instead of a simple hash of the chain tip because blocks and block index entries may not be flushed to disk until after this database is updated. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
